g as an element of architectural design, sustainability concerns, and issues of renovation and modernization. An attractive project section presents examples of successful implementation and offers inspiration for the reader's own practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aFlooring. 7aARCHITECTURE / Decoration & Ornament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2016z9783110482812oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z97831107010120 cprintz978395553282640uhttps://doi.org/10.11129/978395553283340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783955532833423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783955532833.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070101-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DADb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016